  <source>Office of Rare Diseases (ORD)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES:

      I. Assess the efficacy of thioctic acid in treating a single patient with mitochondrial
      myopathy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE: The patient receives one thioctic acid tablet 3 times a day. If patient
      experiences no side effects after 1 week, 2 tablets are administered and given 3 times a day
      over 3 months for compassionate use.

      The patient is followed at weeks 3, 8, and 12.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
