  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        PROTOCOL ENTRY CRITERIA:

        --Disease Characteristics--

          -  Long standing ophthalmoparesis and fatiguable weakness of the limbs

          -  Mild ataxia and no central nervous system involvement

          -  History of mitochondrial DNA deletion and a measurable biochemical defect of the
             respiratory chain

          -  Steady deterioration in skeletal muscle mass and power over 5 years

        --Prior/Concurrent Therapy--

          -  Previous participation in studies of muscle disease natural history (CRC Protocol
             183A)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
